  "title": "Junior Art Educator",
  "description": "<h5>Job Description &amp; Requirements</h5>\n<p><strong>Art Wonderland is an art education studio that provides children of all ages with a fun, warm and nurturing environment to learn art. We engage children through a variety of art mediums and techniques, and connect their learning in the classroom to their everyday environment and experiences.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>We are looking for a bubbly, passionate and self-driven art educator that seeks to inspire our young minds through art, to be future creative thinkers.</strong></p>\n<p><strong>Responsibilities:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Research, conceptualise and design lesson curriculums for ages 2 - 12 years old</li>\n  <li>Leading and teaching studio classes, school programmes with museum partners and external workshops and events</li>\n  <li>Involves working on weekends for classes and events</li>\n  <li>Explore and conceptualise groundbreaking art programmes</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>We are looking for an art educator that:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Loves to work with children and seeks to inspire them</li>\n  <li>Is creative and takes risks, but also well prepared for any situations that arises in the classroom</li>\n  <li>Who agrees with the values and benefits of inquiry-based discussions during art lessons to bring out the creative thinkers in children</li>\n  <li>Seeks out new topics and subjects to turn into a lesson to share with children</li>\n  <li>Looking to be surrounded by other creatives that believe strongly in art education and bringing art closer to children and parents</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Essential Qualifications:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Fresh Graduates are welcome to apply</li>\n  <li>Diploma either in Fine Arts or Art Education</li>\n  <li>Must love to work with children and comfortable speaking to an audience</li>\n  <li>Must have experience with traditional art mediums</li>\n  <li>A plus if you have any experience teaching and interacting with children aged 2 - 12 years old</li>\n</ul>",
